<name>TRANSMISSION</name>
<section id="1000Q_S000E" variety="S000E">
<name>A45DE AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION</name>
<ttl id="1000Q_S000E_7A7ZF_T003T" variety="T003T">
<name>OIL PUMP</name>
<para id="RM0000013B501PX" category="G" type-id="3001K" name-id="AT0G3-08" from="201202">
<name>INSPECTION</name>
<subpara id="RM0000013B501PX_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM0000013B501PX_01_0001" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__000010200000">
<ptxt>INSPECT FRONT OIL PUMP BODY SUB-ASSEMBLY</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C191449" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s2>
<ptxt>Using a caliper gauge, measure the inside diameter of the front oil pump body bush.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Maximum diameter</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>38.19 mm (1.50 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the inside diameter is greater than the maximum, replace the oil pump body.</ptxt>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM0000013B501PX_01_0002" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__000010300000">
<ptxt>INSPECT STATOR SHAFT ASSEMBLY</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C191450" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s2>
<ptxt>Using a caliper gauge, measure the inside diameter of the stator shaft bush.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Maximum diameter</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>23.11 mm (0.910 in.) for front and rear side</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the inside diameter is greater than the maximum, replace the stator shaft.</ptxt>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM0000013B501PX_01_0003" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__000010400000">
<ptxt>INSPECT CLEARANCE OF FRONT OIL PUMP BODY</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C191451" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s2>
<ptxt>Push the driven gear to one side of the body.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Using a feeler gauge, measure the clearance.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard body clearance</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>0.07 to 0.15 mm (0.00276 to 0.00591 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<spec>
<title>Maximum body clearance</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>0.3 mm (0.0118 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the body clearance is greater than the maximum, check the drive gear, driven gear and pump body.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Using a feeler gauge, measure the tip clearance between the driven gear teeth and drive gear teeth.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C191452" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<spec>
<title>Standard tip clearance</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>0.11 to 0.14 mm (0.00433 to 0.00551 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<spec>
<title>Maximum tip clearance</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>0.3 mm (0.0118 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the tip clearance is greater than the maximum, check the drive gear, driven gear and pump body.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Using a straightedge and feeler gauge, measure the side clearance of both gears.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C191453" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<spec>
<title>Standard side clearance</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>0.02 to 0.05 mm (0.000787 to 0.00197 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<spec>
<title>Maximum side clearance</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>0.1 mm (0.00394 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the side clearance is greater than the maximum, check the drive gear, driven gear and pump body. If necessary, replace the drive and driven gears with gears of a different thickness.</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>There are 5 different ranges of thickness for the drive and driven gears.</ptxt>
</atten4>
<spec>
